# Native Language Copy Standards

All i18n strings must feel native — not translated from English. Before writing or editing any translation, ask: *would a monolingual speaker of this language actually say this?*

## The Golden Rule

**Never translate English copy word-for-word.** Rephrase in natural idioms of the target language. When in doubt, use the simpler, shorter, more common word.

---

## Language-Specific Vocabulary

### Telugu (`landing-te.json`)

| Use | Avoid |
|-----|-------|
| జాతకం | kundali, కుండలి |
| జాతక పొందిక | kundali matching, కుండలి మిలాన్ |
| వారఫలం | weekly rashifal, వీక్లీ రాశిఫలం |
| రాశిఫలం | horoscope (transliteration) |
| ఫలితాలు / జాతకఫలం | రీడింగ్ (English loanword) |
| పద్ధతిని | ఫ్రేమ్‌వర్క్‌ (English loanword) |
| నక్షత్రం | star (English) |

- No English words unless they are universally used technical terms with no Telugu equivalent.
- Avoid Hindi loanwords that are not in common Telugu usage.

### Tamil (`landing-ta.json`)

| Use | Avoid |
|-----|-------|
| ஜாதகம் | kundali |
| ஜாதக பொருத்தம் | kundali matching |
| வார ராசிப்பலன் | weekly rashifal |
| பலன் / ஜாதகப் பலன் | வாசிப்பு (literal: reading — unnatural in astrology context) |
| 36 குண பொருத்தம் | 36-point (English) |

- Prefer pure Tamil vocabulary. Classical Sanskrit terms used in Tamil astrology (ஜாதகம், நட்சத்திரம்) are acceptable.
- Do not transliterate English UI words into Tamil script.

### Kannada (`landing-kn.json`)

| Use | Avoid |
|-----|-------|
| ಜಾತಕ | kundali |
| ಜಾತಕ ಹೊಂದಾಣಿಕೆ | kundali matching |
| ವಾರ ಭವಿಷ್ಯ | weekly rashifal |
| ಜಾತಕ ಫಲ / ಭವಿಷ್ಯ | ಓದು (literal: reading — unnatural for horoscope) |
| ಗ್ರಹ ಸ್ಥಿತಿ | planetary position (English) |

- Prefer Kannada-origin or well-established Sanskrit-in-Kannada terms.
- Do not write English words in Kannada script (e.g. avoid ರೀಡಿಂಗ್).

### Hindi (`landing-hi.json`)

| Use | Avoid |
|-----|-------|
| कुंडली मिलान | kundali matching (English mix) |
| फलित / भविष्यफल | रीडिंग (English loanword) |
| साप्ताहिक राशिफल | weekly horoscope (English) |
| शास्त्रीय | classical (English) |
| पद्धति | framework (English) |

- Sanskrit-origin vocabulary is natural and correct in Hindi.
- Avoid mixing English words mid-sentence when a Hindi equivalent exists.

### Marathi (`landing-mr.json`)

| Use | Avoid |
|-----|-------|
| राशीभविष्य | राशिफल (Hindi form — Marathi uses the long ई) |
| जन्मपत्रिका / पत्रिका | (कुंडली is acceptable, but पत्रिका feels more native) |
| मोफत | फ्री (English) |
| अचूक | खच्ची (Urdu/Hindi slang — not standard Marathi) |
| गुण मिलान / जुळणी | matching (English) |

- Use long ई in राशीभविष्य (not short इ like the Hindi राशिफल).
- Marathi has its own vocabulary; prefer it over borrowed Hindi where natural.

---

## All Languages — Structural Rules

1. **No untranslated English strings** in any `landing-*.json` file. Every value must be in the target language. Search for Latin characters before committing.
2. **No mixed-language strings** — do not write `"जन्मपत्रिका और reading"`. Pick one language per string.
3. **Astrological terms** that are classically Sanskrit (नक्षत्र, दशा, लग्न, राशी, भाव) are acceptable in all languages — they are the canonical terms.
4. **UI action words** (button labels, nav items) must always be translated. Never leave `"Compare"`, `"Get Reading"`, or `"Try again"` in English inside a non-English file.
5. **Numbers and symbols** (₹, %, →, ↗, ★) are fine in all languages.

---

## Tone

- Warm, direct, confident — not clinical or bureaucratic.
- Speak to the user as *you* (तुम्ही / నువ్వు / நீ / ನೀವು) — not in the third person.
- Do not use formal register where casual register is natural (e.g. Marathi आपण is overly formal for most UI copy; तुम्ही is appropriate).
